</ul>
<p><a name="References" id="References"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Film_noir&amp;action=edit&amp;section=20" title="Edit section: References">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">References</span></h2>
<div class="references-small references-column-count references-column-count-2" style="-moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> Greenspun (1973), p. 32.</li>
<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> Borde and Chaumeton (2002), p. 2.</li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2" title="">^</a></b> See Dancyger and Rush (2002), p. 68, for a detailed comparison of screwball comedy and film noir.</li>
